updated_at": "2020-04-06T10:12:55Z", "closed_at": "2020-04-06T10:12:54Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "## Issue Description\r\nWhen rebooting the board using `sudo poweroff` and plugging the power back in. The message\r\n```console\r\n@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@\r\n@    WARNING: REMOTE HOST IDENTIFICATION HAS CHANGED!     @\r\n@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@\r\nIT IS POSSIBLE THAT SOMEONE IS DOING SOMETHING NASTY!\r\nSomeone could be eavesdropping on you right now (man-in-the-middle attack)!\r\nIt is also possible that a host key has just been changed.\r\n```\r\nis displayed when trying to ssh to the board over ethernet or wifi.\r\n\r\n## Elk Audio OS version\r\nv0.6.1\r\n## Raspberry Pi Model\r\nRPi 3B+\r\n## How to reproduce\r\n* ssh to board with `ssh mind@the.ip.of.the.board` if it already hasn't been done.\r\n* shutdown the board with `sudo poweroff` and when fully turned of reboot by unplugging and replugging the power.\r\n* try to log in to the board with ssh again.\r\n\r\n", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/elk-audio/elk-pi/issues/2/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/elk-audio/elk-pi/issues/2/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed", "score": 1.0}]}